s of struggle and hope, as one volunteer said, “you see the American story.” For some families, minor mistakes create catastrophes—food stamps cut off, educational opportunities missed, benefits lost. Other families, with the help of volunteers and social supports, escape these traps and take steps toward reaching their dreams. Engaging and eye-opening, We Thought It Would Be Heaven brings readers into the daily lives of Congolese refugees and offers guidance for how activists, workers, and policymakers can help refugee families thrive.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aRefugeesxServices forzUnited States. 0aRefugeeszCongo (Democratic Republic)xSocial conditions. 0aRefugeeszUnited StatesxSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Refugees.2bisacsh1 aKimenyerwa, Honoria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLareau, Annette, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMahamba, Mariamu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalu, Malu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMsafiri, Alain, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMsafiri, Vana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNgoma, Georgette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNgoma, Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2023 Englishz978311131910008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Communic